data.content:
Three things break. Here's each one with the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer takes an expression tree

The signature changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Action<...>`. Your manual expression tree construction won't compile. The fix is a dramatic simplification:

```csharp
// .NET 10 — just use a regular lambda with conditionals
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

All the `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` machinery can be deleted.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Shared property names are now uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF will append a number to disambiguate (e.g., `Street1`). This generates a column-rename migration.

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was mapped to `BillingAddress_City` — it's now `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin the old names explicitly:

```csharp
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, a =>
{
    a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
});
b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, a =>
{
    a.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
});

// For nested complex types:
b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
{
    p.ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress, a =>
    {
        a.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
    });
});
```

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new parameter

All methods like `CommandReaderExecuting` now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
    DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← add this
{ /* logging — use logCommandText for redacted SQL */ }
```

Apply the same to `CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc. — every method on the interface gained this parameter.
